---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const TRIAL_URL = 'https://gymdo-staff-app-main-yzbyzu.laravel.cloud/register';
const DEMO_EMAIL = 'josh@cmdsoftware.com.au';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About - GymDo"
  description="GymDo was built for BJJ academies by someone who trains. Flat pricing, no platform percentage, and features designed around how BJJ gyms actually operate."
>
  <section class="section bg-[#0c2d4e] relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative" data-animate="fade-up">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="badge mb-4" style="background:rgba(34,211,238,0.12);color:#67e8f9;border-color:rgba(34,211,238,0.2);">Our story</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black text-white mb-6">Built from the mat up</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-xl leading-relaxed">
          GymDo is gym management software built by people who love BJJ, for the academies that deserve better than generic platforms and revenue-share pricing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-animate="fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0c2d4e] mb-8">Why we built this</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-500 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            BJJ gym software is broken. Platforms like Mindbody and Glofox were built for yoga studios and general fitness gyms. They have been bolted onto BJJ academies because there was nothing better.
          </p>
          <p>
            The result is clunky software that doesn't understand belt promotions, doesn't track the attendance signals that matter for BJJ retention, and charges a percentage of your membership revenue on top of a monthly fee.
          </p>
          <p>
            GymDo is purpose-built for Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. Belt tracking follows IBJJF standards. Retention scoring reflects how BJJ members actually drift. Pricing is flat because we grow when your gym grows, not when you collect dues.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're starting with a pilot program in Queensland with five BJJ academies. If you're running a gym on spreadsheets, Kicksite, or generic software, we'd love to have a conversation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center mb-12" data-animate="fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0c2d4e] mb-4">What we stand for</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto" data-animate="stagger">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="text-[#0c2d4e] font-bold mb-2">No platform cut</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Flat monthly fee. GymDo doesn't take a platform percentage on top of your revenue. Standard Stripe processing applies, same as anywhere.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="text-[#0c2d4e] font-bold mb-2">BJJ-first</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Every feature is designed around how BJJ academies operate. Not adapted from a general gym template.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="text-[#0c2d4e] font-bold mb-2">Founder-direct</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">When you email us with a question or feature request, you're talking to the person who built it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-[#0c2d4e]">
    <div class="container text-center" data-animate="fade-up">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-white mb-4">Join the pilot</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        We're onboarding BJJ academies now. 30-day free trial, and if you're not happy in the first 30 days of billing, we'll refund you.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href={TRIAL_URL} class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Start free trial</a>
        <a href={`mailto:${DEMO_EMAIL}`} class="btn btn-outline-white btn-lg">Get in touch</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
